# JID Platform вАФ Cursor Rules
# ўЕўЖЎµЎ© ЎђўРЎѓ | Next.js 14.2.15 + TypeScript + Supabase

## Project Identity
- Product: JID (ЎђўРЎѓ) вАФ Arabic-first employment & mentorship platform
- Stack: Next.js 14.2.15 App Router, TypeScript (strict), Tailwind CSS, Supabase (Postgres/Auth/Realtime/Storage)
- Package manager: pnpm (never npm or yarn)
- Database: Supabase вАФ NEVER use Firebase

## TypeScript Rules
- `strict: true` and `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true` are mandatory вАФ never weaken tsconfig
- No `any` вАФ use `unknown` + type guards or Zod parsing
- Prefer `type` imports: `import type { Foo } from '...'`
- All env vars must go through `src/lib/env.ts` Zod schema вАФ never read `process.env` directly in app code
- Path alias: always use `@/` imports (e.g. `@/lib/env`, `@/config/design-tokens`)

## React & Next.js Conventions
- Default to Server Components вАФ add `'use client'` only when browser APIs, hooks, or interactivity require it
- Use `next/navigation` (not `next/router`) for routing
- Use `next/image` for all images; Supabase storage URLs are pre-configured in next.config.mjs
- Never expose `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to client code or `NEXT_PUBLIC_` vars
- Colocate server actions in `actions.ts` files next to their route segment

## Styling & Design System
- Use JID design tokens from `src/config/design-tokens.ts` вАФ never hardcode hex colors in components
- Tailwind classes: `jid-olive`, `jid-gold`, `jid-beige`, `jid-ink`, `jid-line` (and their scales)
- RTL is the default: root layout must have `lang="ar" dir="rtl"`
- Fonts: IBM Plex Sans Arabic (primary), Archivo (Latin fallback)
- Background: `jid-beige`, text: `jid-ink`, accent/CTA: `jid-gold`, borders: `jid-line`

## Supabase Rules
- Browser client: `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` (createBrowserClient from @supabase/ssr)
- Server client: `src/lib/supabase/server.ts` (createServerClient with cookies)
- Admin/service client: `src/lib/supabase/admin.ts` вАФ server-only, uses service role key
- All tables must have RLS enabled; policies must match the access model
- Realtime: use `supabase.channel().on('postgres_changes', ...)` for live subscriptions
- Migrations live in `supabase/migrations/` вАФ never alter applied migrations

## File Structure
```
src/
  app/           # App Router pages & layouts (route groups: (auth), (individual), (entity), (staff), (admin))
  components/    # UI components (ui/ for shadcn primitives, feature folders for domain)
  lib/           # Utilities, Supabase clients, env, validations
  config/        # Design tokens, constants
  hooks/         # Client-side hooks only
  i18n/          # next-intl configuration
  types/         # Shared TypeScript types
supabase/
  migrations/    # SQL migrations (ordered, never edit applied ones)
  functions/     # Edge Functions
scripts/         # Dev/CI scripts (check-env.ts, seed scripts)
```

## i18n
- Use `next-intl` for all user-facing strings
- Default locale: `ar` (Arabic RTL)
- Message files: `messages/ar.json`, `messages/en.json`

## Security
- Never commit `.env.local` or secrets
- Run `pnpm check-env` before starting dev server
- Validate all user input with Zod schemas in `src/lib/validations/`
- Audit sensitive actions to `audit_logs` table

## Git & Commits
- Conventional commits enforced by commitlint (feat/fix/docs/chore/etc.)
- Pre-commit: lint-staged runs prettier + eslint
- Branch naming: `feat/`, `fix/`, `chore/` prefixes

## What NOT to Do
- Do not use Firebase (database is Supabase)
- Do not create pages/components without being asked in the current phase
- Do not bypass RLS with service role key in client code
- Do not use inline styles for colors вАФ use Tailwind + design tokens
- Do not use `console.log` in production code вАФ use structured logging or remove
